article.description: St. Francis Brooklyn beats Mount St. Vincent 83-54
article.headline: St. Francis Brooklyn beats Mount St. Vincent 83-54
article.linkText: St. Francis Brooklyn beats Mount St. Vincent 83-54
article.story: BROOKLYN HEIGHTS, N.Y. -- Wayne Martin scored 17 points in 18 minutes on 7-of-8 shooting and had nine rebounds as St. Francis Brooklyn won its home opener against Mount St. Vincent 83-54 on Wednesday. St. Francis (4-3) held Mount St. Vincent to only 30 percent shooting and 3 of 16 from 3-point range. St. Francis' opponents have shot 18 of 82 (22 percent) from the arc this season. Jalen Cannon chipped in 16 points and eight rebounds and Ben Mockford made 3 of 4 3-point attempts. The Terriers took a 7-5 lead on Mockford's first 3 and never trailed from there. St. Francis led 45-36 at the half and opened the second half on a 10-2 run. Brandon Serrano scored 12 of his team-high 14 points in the first half for Mount St. Vincent (1-3). Gerard Fraser had nine points and nine rebounds.
